{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> μακρός</b>, ά, όν [ᾰ <br /> by nature], <b>long</b>, whether of Space or Time, <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> of Space, <br /><Level3><b>__I.1</b></Level3> in length, <b>long</b>, δόρυ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 7.140 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; νέες, νῆες μ. <b>ships of war</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.21, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.41, etc. (_collective_ in _sing._, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 380); πλοῖα μ. 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.30, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.14 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπὶ τὰ -ότερα measured by <b>the longer sides</b>, i. e. <b>length-wise</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.50 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὰ μ. τείχη the <b>long</b> walls of Athens, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.71, etc.; ἐν τῷ μακρῷ σκέλει τῷ πὸτ τῷ Ποτειδανίῳ “SIG” 247 iii 11 (Delph., 4th c.BC)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἡ μακρά (i.e. γραμμή), line traced by δικασταί to indicate the heavier penalty, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 106 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὁ μ. δρόμος the <b>long-distance</b> torch-race, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 1068.9 (Patmos, 3rd-2nd c.BC), +others, “OGI” 339.83 (Sestos, 2nd c.BC). \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> in height, <b>tall, high</b>, μ. Ὄλυμπος, οὔρεα, δένδρεα, κίων, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.193, 13.18, 9.541, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 1.127, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of a man, μακρότερον καὶ πάσσονα θῆκεν ἰδέσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8.20, compare 18.195; μ. πύκτης “PLond.” 3.1158.6 (3rd c.AD). \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>] <br /><Level4><b>__I.2.b</b></Level4> reversely, <b>deep</b>, φρείατα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 21.197; φάραγξ 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 8.17. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.3</b></Level3> in distance, <b>long, far, remote</b>, κέλευθος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.358; οἶμος 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 290; ναυτιλίαι 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.1; στόλος 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 490 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; μ. ἐπιβοήθειαι <b>long</b> marches to aid, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 5.4.47 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>remote</b>, ἀποικία [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 814 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; τὰ μακρότατα the <b>remotest parts</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.32: frequently in _neuter_ _sing._ and _plural_ as \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <i>adverb</i>, μακρὰ βιβάς, βιβάσθων, with <b>long</b> strides, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 7.213, 13.809 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; μακρὰ ῥίψαις, δισκήσαις, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 1.45, “I.” 2.35; - ότερον σφενδονᾶν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 3.4.16 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μακρὸν ἀῧσαι, βοᾶν, to shout <b>so as to be heard afar</b>, i. e. <b>loudly</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 3.81, 2.224; μακρὰ μεμυκώς 18.580; μακρὸν ἠχεῖν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 329a; κλάειν σε μακρὰ κελεύσας 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 433 (see. κλαίω and below see)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; later by analogy, μακρὰ χαίρειν φράσας τῷ ναυπηγῷ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Nav.” 2, compare “Apol.” 3, +others, 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 46.3 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; compare μακράν. <br /><Level3><b>__I.4</b></Level3> generally, <b>large in size</b> or <b>degree, great</b>, ἤπειρος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 75; ὄλβος 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 2.26; πλοῦτος 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 130; τιμήματα 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1278a23, compare 1297b4 (_superlative_); οὐσία [prev. work] 1290b16, 1321a11; μακροτέρα ἀρετά 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 4(3).13; ἐλπίσαντες μακρότερα μὲν τῆς δυνάμεως, ἐλάσσω δὲ τῆς βουλήσεως 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.39 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μ. τραπεζῖται, perhaps <b>big</b> bankers, <b>Cat.Codex Astr.</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7.222. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.5</b></Level3> <i>dative</i> μακρῷ, to strengthen <i>comparative</i> and <i>superlative</i>, <b>by far</b>, μ. πρῶτος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.34; ἄριστος μ. [prev. author] 9.71; ἀσθενεστέρα μ. 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 514, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Philebus” 66e; μ. μάλιστα 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.171, compare 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 30, etc.; κάκιστα δὴ μ. 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 895 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: also with Verbs implying comparison, ἀριστεύει μ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 890 (Lyric poetry), compare 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 1.2. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> of Time, <b>long</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"(8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus only in 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey”), ἤματα, νύξ, 10.470, 11.373 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; αἰών see reading in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 3.75; μ. χρόνος 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.32, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐ μ. χρόνου for no <b>long</b> time, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 1078, etc.; διὰ μ. χρόνου 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 741 (troch.); ἐν χρόνῳ μ. 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 88, etc.; δι᾽ αἰῶνος μ. 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 582 (Lyric poetry); τὸν μ. βίον [prev. author] “Pr.” 449; τοῦ μ. βίου 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 473 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μηνὶ -ότερος <b>by</b> a month, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.32 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μακρῷ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" (compare 1.5) πρότερον 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 8.958 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; μ. ἐέλδωρ a <b>long-cherished</b> wish, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 23.54 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; μ. γόοι, ὀδύρματα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 375, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 297. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>long, tedious</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 4.33, etc.; λόγοι 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 1335, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.60, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μακρὰν ἔοικε λέξειν (i.e. ῥῆσιν) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 382; οὐδὲ εἷς Ὅμηρον εἴρηκεν μακρόν 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus 97.7 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μακρόν [ἐστι] with <i>infinitive</i>, Latin <i>longum est</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 6(5).56; μ. ἂν εἴη γράφειν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Agesilaus” 7.1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. <i>adverb</i> - ρῶς, λέγεσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Antiphanes Comicus 268 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: <i>comparative</i> -ότερον, ποιεῖς you are taking <b>too long,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Zenon Papyri du Caire 48.4 (3rd c.BC),compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Philippides Comicus 21. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> Grammars, <b>long</b> in quantity, φωνήεντα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Poetica” 1458a11, 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “de Compositione Verborum” 15 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; μακρά (i.e. συλλαβή), ἡ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Apollonius Dyscolus Grammaticus “de Pronominibus;” 92.12; ἡ φύσει μ. [prev. author] “Adv.” 179.16 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]: <i>comparative</i>, φωνήεντι μακροτέρῳ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Poetica” 1458a1 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; also μακρά (i.e. προσῳδία), ἡ, <b>mark of long quantity</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Sextus Empiricus Philosophus “adversus Mathematicos” 1.113, 2nd c.BC: Dionysius Thrax Grammaticus “Supp.” 674.7; ᾱ μακρόν 2nd c.AD: Apollonius Dyscolus Grammaticus “de Pronominibus;” 112. 6. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>neuter</i> with Preps. in <i>adverbial</i> sense, διὰ μακροῦ (i.e. χρόνου) after <b>a long time, long delayed</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 320, “Ph.” 1069 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐ διὰ μακροῦ not <b>long after</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.15, 91, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus Alcaeus2.151b (also of place, οὐ διὰ μ. τῆς Ῥώμης 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 9.56); διὰ μακρῶν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 420.1; διὰ μακρᾶς 3rd-2nd c.BC: Phalaris Epistolographus “Epistulae - Epistolographi” 69.1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but διὰ μακρῶν <b>at great length</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 449b, etc.; διὰ μακροτέρων 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 4.106 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μικρῷ διὰ μ. at somewhat <b>greater length</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1279b11. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> ὄλβος οὐκ ἐς μακρὸν ἔρχεται for no <b>long time</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 3.105 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐς τὰ μακρότατα to the <b>utmost</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.31; see at {μακράν} 11. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.3</b></Level3> ἐπὶ μακρόν <b>far, a long way</b>, πορεύεσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 5.4.47 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of Time, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Hymnus in Delum” 255; ὅσον ἐπὶ μακρότατον οἷοί τε ἐγενόμεθα ἐξικέσθαι ἀκοῇ 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.16, compare 2.34 (ἐπὶ omitted 1.171 codices)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τοσόνδε ἐπὶ μ. ἐπυθόμην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 2.29 \">Refs</a>]; ἐπὶ μακρότερον <b>yet more</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.41. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> regular <i>comparative</i> and <i>superlative</i>, see above: irregular <i>comparative</i> μάσσων, <i>superlative</i> μήκιστος, (see entry). <br /><Level2><b>__V</b></Level2> <i>adverb</i> -ρῶς <b>at great length</b>, opposed to συντόμως, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1416b4 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>slowly</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 3.51.2 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; μ. ἔχειν τοῖν σκέλοιν have <b>long</b> legs, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “de gymnastica” 31 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; of pronunciation, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “de Compositione Verborum” 15; μ. ἐκφέρειν συλλαβήν 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 13.1.68: but the \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>] <i>adverb</i> is usually expressed by <i>neuter</i> μακρόν or μακρά, compare above [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1.3 \">Refs</a>]; μακρὰ κλάειν to howl <b>loudly</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 211; οἰμώξει μ. [prev. author] “Av.” 1207, “Pl.” 111; ὀτοτύζεσθαι μ. [prev. author] “Lys.” 520 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τί μακρὰ δεῖ λέγει; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Antiphanes Comicus 33.5; also by μακράν (see. entry); or by _neuter_ with a _preposition_, see above 111 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: for <i>comparative</i> and <i>superlative</i> of the <i>adverb</i>, see at {μακροτέρως, μακροτάτω}: <i>neuter</i> <i>plural</i> -ότερα as <i>adverb</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 250c, +others\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] — Fem. μακρά not to be confused with μάκρα (which see). (Cf. Avest. <b>mas</b>-'long', Latin <i>ma?~Xcer.</i>)","strongNumber":"G3117","accentedUnicode":"μακρός","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G3113","matchingForm":"μακρόθεν","stepTransliteration":"makrothen","gloss":"from afar","_zh_tw_Gloss":"遠處","_es_Gloss":"desde la distancia","_zh_Gloss":"远处"},{"strongNumber":"G3117","matchingForm":"μακρός","stepTransliteration":"makros","gloss":"long/distant","_zh_tw_Gloss":"很長","_es_Gloss":"largo/distante","_zh_Gloss":"很长"},{"strongNumber":"G3372","matchingForm":"μῆκος","stepTransliteration":"mēkos","gloss":"length","_zh_tw_Gloss":"長","_es_Gloss":"longitud","_zh_Gloss":"长"}],"shortDef":"lengthy, long; distant, far away","mediumDef":"lengthy, long; distant, far away <br /><b>long;</b>, of space, <b>far, distant, remote,</b> <ref='Luk.15.13; 19:12'>Lk. 15:13; 19:12</ref>; of time, <b>of long duration,lengthy</b> <ref='Mrk.12.40'>Mk. 12:40</ref>; <ref='Luk.20.47'>Lk. 20:47</ref>*","stepGloss":"long/distant","stepTransliteration":"makros","count":15,"_es_Definition":"largo ; distante, lejos","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 漫長的<br> 1a) 指距離<br> 1b) 指時間","_zh_Definition":"1) 漫长的<br> 1a) 指距离<br> 1b) 指时间","_step_Type":"word","_stepDetailLexicalTag":"[[\"meaning\",\"G3117\",\"long/distant\",15,\"μακρός\"],[\"in the form\",\"G3112\",\"far\",0,\"μακράν\"]]","_vi_Definition":"(cầu nguyện) dài; (một nơi) xa; gian dài","_zh_tw_Gloss":"很長","_es_Gloss":"largo/distante","_zh_Gloss":"很长"}]}